data.title: Chiefs training camp: Updated 53-man roster prediction heading into preseason

data.text:
The Kansas City Chiefs have looked ready for action during their training camp at Missouri Western State University, and as the preseason draws near, the defending champions have seen some players put together excellent performances at practice, while others have struggled to find their footing.

Though the Chiefs haven't yet faced the test of a live game, their first exhibition matchup against the Jacksonville Jaguars is slated for Saturday, August 10, leaving only a few more workouts for potential contributors to rise up on Kansas City's depth chart.

Every season presents new obstacles for teams to overcome, and it seems that the Chiefs will have some difficult decisions to make when they cut their roster to 53 players after their three games in August.
